definition: car/vehicle/CL:輛|辆[liang4]/machine/to shape with a lathe/Kangxi radical 159

sentences.english: A wooden passenger car was abandoned at back yard of Wu-Shu-Lin Depot.
sentences.chinese: 廢棄於烏樹林車庫後方的糖鐵木製客車。

sentences.english: Cleaned out the garage and sold 2 old dehumidifiers on eBay.
sentences.chinese: 收拾了車庫，在易趣上賣掉了兩臺舊除溼機。

sentences.english: I see this kid in front of a garage and show him the money.
sentences.chinese: 我看到一個孩子站在車庫前，就給他看這些錢。

sentences.english: Though badly damaged by fire, the bus tried to make for its garage.
sentences.chinese: 這輛車雖被大火嚴重燒壞，仍努力開回車庫。

sentences.english: There's too much for the fridge. I'll put it in the garage. It's cold there.
sentences.chinese: 冰箱裏東西太多了，我來把它放到車庫裏去，那裏冷。

sentences.english: Consumers will have to pay more. The motor and garage trades will be harmed.
sentences.chinese: 消費者會增加開支，汽車和車庫生意也會受損。

sentences.english: An employee drives the Rolls into the bank's underground garage and parks it there.
sentences.chinese: 一個工作人員將這輛車開入銀行的地下車庫並且停好。

sentences.english: According to the new code for underground garages, discusses design of smoke control and extraction systems in underground garages.
sentences.chinese: 結合規範要求，探討了地下汽車庫防排煙設計問題。

sentences.english: She reversed her car into the garage.
Two further bedrooms are situated above one of the ground-floor bedrooms and the adjacent garage.
sentences.chinese: 還有兩間臥室位於一層臥室和鄰近車庫的上面。

sentences.english: The idea was conceived and developed in Jobs garage.
sentences.chinese: 這個想法是在喬布斯的車庫裏構思發展的。

sentences.english: I don't recommend you do this in your garage at home tonight.
sentences.chinese: 我並不建議大家今晚回家後在車庫裏去試驗。

sentences.english: Trucks may only park inside closed garages.
sentences.chinese: 卡車只可停在關閉的車庫內。

sentences.english: Your marketing funnel operates just like a conventional funnel you use in you kitchen or garage.
sentences.chinese: 你就像傳統營銷漏斗運轉在你的廚房用漏斗或車庫。

sentences.english: He did this all from his 3 car garage!
sentences.chinese: 他是通過他那3個車庫做到這一切的。
